Description: Fragment of oval handle of a Rhodian pottery transport amphora at neck join. Clay medium, orange-buff; some mica; cream slip. Rectangular, rounded stamp with Greek inscription.
Curator's comments: Pencil '9H'? Petrie noted several such stamps in his 1884-5 diary (EES Archive XVII 47). Name Timarchos. From the same die as 1925,0119.144b and 554a and 2011,5003.334.
Bibliographic references: Villing et al 2013-2015 / Naukratis: Greeks in Egypt (JB.0435)
